18/05/2007
NEUM, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- Parliament speakers from countries in the Adriatic-Ionian Initiative conferred on Thursday (May 17th), in a bid to co-ordinate and boost regional co-operation in the field of environmental protection. The members are Albania, BiH, Croatia, Greece, Italy, Serbia, Montenegro and Slovenia. Presiding over the Initiative this year, the BiH Assembly is hosting the gathering. Lower House Speaker Beriz Belkic said participants discussed and offered recommendations on protecting the Adriatic and Ionian seas, especially in the context of developing tourism, naval co-operation and communications. (Fena, RTRS, NTV Hayat - 17/05/07)
